text: Wuhan Jianghan University F.C. (Chinese: 武汉江汉大学足球俱乐部) is a Chinese professional football club located in Wuhan. They compete in the Chinese Women's Super League, and their home stadium is Tazihu Football Training Centre. == History == Wuhan Jianghan University F.C. was founded in 2001 as a cooperation between Jianghan University and the Wuhan football association. In 2017, the team won the first honour in its history, winning the 2017 China Women's League One title to achieve promotion to the China Women's Super League for the first time in its history. In the 2018 China Women's Super League season, they finished fourth. At the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup they had five representatives in the China national team selected for the competition. Following the tournament, they re-signed former player Wang Shuang after a season at Paris Saint-Germain ahead of the 2019 China Women's Super League campaign. == Current Squad == Updated: 11 November 2020 == Honours == === Leagues === * Chinese Women's League One : Champions (1): 2017 China Women's League One == References == Category:Chinese Women's Super League clubs Category:2001 establishments in China Category:Association football clubs established in 2001 Category:Sport in Wuhan Category:Sport in Hubei
